.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.push_thread_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make `conf` the active configuration for this thread.\nThread-local configuration always overrides process-wide\nconfiguration.\n\nThis should be used like:\n\n```\nconf = make_conf()\ndispatching_config.push_thread_config(conf)\ntry:\n    ... do stuff ...\nfinally:\n    dispatching_config.pop_thread_config(conf)\n```\n"]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.pop_thread_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Remove a thread-local configuration.  If `conf` is given,\nit is checked against the popped configuration and an error\nis emitted if they don't match.\n"]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig._pop_from", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lst", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.push_process_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Like push_thread_config, but applies the configuration to\nthe entire process."]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.pop_process_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.__getattr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.current_conf", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.__contains__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig.__setitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig._constructor_lock", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["This is a configuration object that can be used globally,\nimported, have references held onto.  The configuration may differ\nby thread (or may not).\n\nSpecific configurations are registered (and deregistered) either\nfor the process or for threads."]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.ConfigMiddleware", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "paste.deploy.config.ConfigMiddleware.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "application", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This delegates all requests to `application`, adding a *copy*\nof the configuration `config`."]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.ConfigMiddleware.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "environ", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_response", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A WSGI middleware that adds a `paste.config` key to the request\nenvironment, as well as registering the configuration temporarily\n(for the length of the request) with `paste.CONFIG`.\n"]}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.PrefixMiddleware", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "paste.deploy.config.PrefixMiddleware.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "global_conf", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prefix", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "translate_forwarded_server", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "force_port", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "scheme", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.PrefixMiddleware.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "environ", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_response", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Translate a given prefix into a SCRIPT_NAME for the filtered\napplication.\n\nPrefixMiddleware provides a way to manually override the root prefix\n(SCRIPT_NAME) of your application for certain, rare situations.\n\nWhen running an application under a prefix (such as '/james') in\nFastCGI/apache, the SCRIPT_NAME environment variable is automatically\nset to to the appropriate value: '/james'. Pylons' URL generating\nfunctions, such as url_for, always take the SCRIPT_NAME value into account.\n\nOne situation where PrefixMiddleware is required is when an application\nis accessed via a reverse proxy with a prefix. The application is accessed\nthrough the reverse proxy via the the URL prefix '/james', whereas the\nreverse proxy forwards those requests to the application at the prefix '/'.\n\nThe reverse proxy, being an entirely separate web server, has no way of\nspecifying the SCRIPT_NAME variable; it must be manually set by a\nPrefixMiddleware instance. Without setting SCRIPT_NAME, url_for will\ngenerate URLs such as: '/purchase_orders/1', when it should be\ngenerating: '/james/purchase_orders/1'.\n\nTo filter your application through a PrefixMiddleware instance, add the\nfollowing to the '\\[app:main\\]' section of your .ini file:\n\n```ini\nfilter-with = proxy-prefix\n\n[filter:proxy-prefix]\nuse = egg:PasteDeploy#prefix\nprefix = /james\n```\n\nThe name `proxy-prefix` simply acts as an identifier of the filter\nsection; feel free to rename it.\n\nAlso, unless disabled, the `X-Forwarded-Server` header will be\ntranslated to the `Host` header, for cases when that header is\nlost in the proxying.  Also `X-Forwarded-Host`,\n`X-Forwarded-Scheme`, and `X-Forwarded-Proto` are translated.\n\nIf `force_port` is set, SERVER_PORT and HTTP_HOST will be\nrewritten with the given port.  You can use a number, string (like\n'80') or the empty string (whatever is the default port for the\nscheme).  This is useful in situations where there is port\nforwarding going on, and the server believes itself to be on a\ndifferent port than what the outside world sees.\n\nYou can also use `scheme` to explicitly set the scheme (like\n`scheme = https`).\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "paste.deploy.config.CONFIG", "xref": {"fqname": "paste.deploy.config.CONFIG", "project": null}}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.ConfigMiddleware", "xref": {"fqname": "paste.deploy.config.ConfigMiddleware", "project": null}}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig", "xref": {"fqname": "paste.deploy.config.DispatchingConfig", "project": null}}, {"name": "paste.deploy.config.PrefixMiddlewar